Fixed shellcheck SC2004: Removed unnecessary $ in arithmetic expressions.

Problem: Used $(($ OPTIND - 1)) which unnecessarily escapes variable in
arithmetic context.

Solution: Changed to shift $((OPTIND - 1)) which is the proper way to reference
variables in arithmetic expressions without the extra $ prefix.

Applied to git-arch.sh. Arithmetic expressions already expand variables without
needing $ prefix.

/Claude-haiku@4.5
